description:
Maritime International in Montreal is a division of L3Harris, a leading global supplier of naval handling and visual landing aids systems, control and simulation solutions products and services for the marine, power generation and space and civil sectors. Headquartered in Montreal, Canada, Maritime International has operating units located in Australia, Germany, India, Italy, Malaysia, the United Kingdom and The United States Canada | L3Harris™ Fast. Forward..
We take pride in our organization and are excited about our future! Our success is primarily driven by our personnel’s talents, expertise, innovative skills and commitment to making Maritime International a solid, growing division, dedicated to excellence in technology and to supplying our customers with high-quality products and services. 
ENGINEERING (SOFTWARE, ELECTRICAL MECHANICAL, SYSTEMS, COMPUTER), QUALITY ASSURANCE, QUALITY CONTROL, CO-OP AND INTERNSHIPS Maritime International is committed to supporting academic excellence and lifelong learning by providing a meaningful work experience that complements a student’s career direction. The objective of the Maritime International student co-op program is to provide a feeder system of highly qualified and highly motivated students for permanent hire upon graduating into Maritime International or another L3Harris organization. These positions are located in Montreal and Ottawa.
OVERVIEW

Exciting Opportunities in the following fields: 

Research and preparation of engineering drawings, and coordination of design activities with Systems Engineering, Manufacturing, and Production to ensure that designs meet requirements at minimum cost;
Apply computer science, engineering, and mathematical analysis concepts and principles in the development of software for the target application;

Collaborate with experienced cross-disciplinary L3Harris engineers to conceive, design, and bring innovative products and services to clients;
Work on our Automated Test pipeline and support the software documentation;
Work closely with cross-functional members of the engineering organization to develop and evaluate interfaces between hardware and software, and operational performance requirements and design of the overall system.

BENEFITS OF THE MARITIME INTERNATIONAL CO-OP PROGRAM

Gain real work experience while attending college or university;
Receive a competitive hourly salary with flexible work schedules;
Receive career and development training;
Eligible to Physical Wellness Program (50% reimbursement up to 300$ per year);
Work with leading-edge technology and forward-thinking people;
Work on challenging and relevant projects in a dynamic work environment; 
Participation to our PEER Onboarding Program for incoming new hires and their managers;
Canadian Industrial Leadership Award (CILA) women program eligibility Home - Canadian Industrial Leadership Award (cilaward.ca).
